messages.msgSnippet: hi jenny, i think all groups get stuck in their emotional eddies but it s my opinion that it s more important that people be heard then it is to hurry past a
messages.messageBody:
hi jenny,

i think all groups get stuck in their 'emotional eddies' but it's my
opinion that it's more important that people be heard then it is to
hurry past a topic. and when there are nearing 400 member
discussions are bound to take a bit of time and cover many different
points of view - many which are conflicting. sorry you walked into a
discussion not to your liking but feel free to start your own topic -
i'm sure people will jump in and have something to say.

-susan
austin, tx
